OL,3,CWhat is the Spring Statement and why
OL,4,Cdoes it matter?
OL,6,FThe difficult economic climate and the
OL,7,Ffact that the #9.9 billion headroom
OL,8,FReeves left herself in October looks
OL,9,Flikely to have been wiped out, means
OL,10,Fin order to avoid breaking her own
OL,11,Ffiscal rules, she'll need to find
OL,12,Fmoney through cuts.
OL,14,FThe chancellor has said she will not
OL,15,Fraise taxes in the Spring Statement,
OL,16,Fso that means cutting spending is the
OL,17,Fonly lever she can pull to stick
OL,18,Fwithin her rules.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/15
