OL,3,CWhat is the Spring Statement and why
OL,4,Cdoes it matter?
OL,6,FThe cost of government borrowing has
OL,7,Frisen because of high interest rates,
OL,8,Fgrowth projections have been
OL,9,Fdowngraded, and international events
OL,10,Fsuch as the threat of Trump's tariffs
OL,11,Fhave meant there's a lot less cash for
OL,12,FReeves to play with.
OL,14,FWhat are the fiscal rules and why are
OL,15,Fthey so important to Reeves?
OL,17,FRachel Reeves' two main fiscal rules
OL,18,Fare that debt should be falling as a
OL,19,Fshare of national income by 2030, and
OL,20,Fthe government shouldn't borrow to
OL,21,Ffund day-to-day spending.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/15
